report_tracker_justification: GitHub issues are used for tracking individual issues.
report_process_justification: Bug reports are submitted as GitHub issues: <https://github.com/AcademySoftwareFoundation/OpenColorIO/issues>
report_responses_justification: The majority of bug reports have been acknowledged with a response or assigned tag in the last 12 months.
enhancement_responses_justification: The majority of enhancement requests have been acknowledged with a response or assigned tag in the last 12 months.
report_archive_justification: GitHub issue history is archived and publicly searchable: <https://github.com/AcademySoftwareFoundation/OpenColorIO/issues>
vulnerability_report_process_justificati: Reporting procedures published in security policy file in repository: <https://github.com/AcademySoftwareFoundation/OpenColorIO/blob/main/SECURITY.md>
vulnerability_report_private_justificati:
- Private vulnerability reporting is supported via the private email alias: <security@opencolorio.org>
- Private reporting procedures are documented in security policy file in repository: <https://github.com/AcademySoftwareFoundation/OpenColorIO/blob/main/SECURITY.md>
vulnerability_report_response_justificat: There have been no vulnerabilities reported.
build_floss_tools_justification: OCIO is buildable using only FLOSS tools.
test_justification:
- Test suite: <https://github.com/AcademySoftwareFoundation/OpenColorIO/tree/main/tests>
- Most source files have robust test coverage
test_invocation_justification: Test suite is invocable with CTest on all platforms.
test_most_justification: SonarCloud static analysis reports ~80% test coverage: <https://sonarcloud.io/component_measures?id=AcademySoftwareFoundation_OpenColorIO&metric=coverage&view=list>
test_policy_justification: Relevant tests being added to the automated test suite with major new functionality is an informal requirement for merging a PR.
tests_are_added_justification: All recent commits adding major changes have thorough test coverage, as evidenced in the project commit history: <https://github.com/AcademySoftwareFoundation/OpenColorIO/commits/main>
tests_documented_added_justification:
Test policy and implementation details need to be added to:

- Contribution file: <https://github.com/AcademySoftwareFoundation/OpenColorIO/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md>
- Unit Tests: <https://opencolorio.readthedocs.io/en/latest/guides/contributing/contributing.html#unit-tests>
warnings_justification:
- All Linux and macOS continuous integration builds enable -Wall (enable all compiler warnings) and -Werror (treat all compiler warnings as errors).
- SonarCloud static analysis is used for finding code quality errors: <https://sonarcloud.io/dashboard?id=AcademySoftwareFoundation_OpenColorIO>
warnings_fixed_justification: Warnings are actively addressed with fixes or disabled in CMake with an accompanying comment to explain false positives or other justification.
warnings_strict_justification: Need to re-enable strict warning detection in CI builds.
know_secure_design_justification: A designated security expert for the project has not been made public, however all of the TSC members have knowledge of how to design secure software.
know_common_errors_justification:
- TSC has discussed this in detail. 
- Security policy file outlining where errors could occur, and guidelines for preventing them, published in repository: <https://github.com/AcademySoftwareFoundation/OpenColorIO/blob/main/SECURITY.md>

delivery_mitm_justification: Uses GitHub releases for delivery mechanism.
vulnerabilities_fixed_60_days_justificat: There have been no publicly known vulnerabilities.
vulnerabilities_critical_fixed_justifica: No critical vulnerabilities have been reported, but they should be fixed rapidly if and when they are.
static_analysis_justification: SonarCloud static analysis is run nightly: <https://sonarcloud.io/dashboard?id=AcademySoftwareFoundation_OpenColorIO>
static_analysis_common_vulnerabilities_j: SonarCloud static analysis includes rule to look for vulnerabilities and security hotspots.
static_analysis_fixed_justification: No vulnerabilities have been discovered yet by SonarCloud, but future vulnerabilities will be addressed as quickly as possible once confirmed.
dynamic_analysis_justification: Beneficial to implement dynamic analysis once static analysis is implemented.
dynamic_analysis_enable_assertions_justi: Unit tests contain many run-time assertions that could be checked by dynamic analysis while running tests.
dynamic_analysis_fixed_justification: Need to implement dynamic analysis to detect possible vulnerabilities.
crypto_weaknesses_justification: Software has no need to directly use cryptographic capabilities.
test_continuous_integration_justificatio: Continuous integration is implemented with GitHub Actions for Linux, macOS, and Windows. Build and tests are run automatically with every PR commit and merge.

- ocio-dev and ocio-user mail lists facilitate public discussion, are searchable, and each thread has a URL.
